(112, 31, 5, 'Kawal Tiger Reserve', 'Kawal Tiger Reserve is one of Telangana\\\'s premier wildlife sanctuaries, spread across 893 sq km of pristine deciduous forests. Home to tigers, leopards, gaur, cheetal, sambar, and numerous bird species. The reserve features diverse terrain including hills, valleys, and water bodies.', 'Kawal Tiger Reserve.jpg', ': Jannaram, Mancherial District Coordinates: 19.3023Â° N, 79.2151Â° E', 'â€¢	Kawal Forest Rest House â€¢	Jannaram Forest Guest House â€¢	Nature Camp at Kawal â€¢	Mancherial Town Hotels (30 km away)', 'https://kawaltiger.com/', '1.	Jannaram Village (12 km) 2.	Pranahita Wildlife Sanctuary (45 km) 3.	Pochera Waterfalls (60 km) 4.	Gandhari Fort (35 km)', 'â€¢	Forest Department Canteen â€¢	Local restaurants in Jannaram â€¢	Traditional Telugu cuisine at Mancherial â€¢	Highway dhabas on NH-44', ''),
(113, 31, 5, 'Pocheram Wildlife Sanctuary', 'A hidden gem featuring dry deciduous forests and grasslands. Known for blackbucks, wolves, foxes, and various species of deer. The sanctuary is particularly famous for its bird population, including migratory birds during winter.', 'Pocheram Wildlife Sanctuary.jpg', 'Location: Medak District Coordinates: 18.1456Â° N, 78.2954Â° E', 'â€¢	Pocheram Forest Rest House â€¢	Medak Tourist Lodge â€¢	Private resorts in Medak â€¢	Homestays in nearby villages', 'https://medak.telangana.gov.in/pocharam-sanctuary/', '1.	Medak Fort (25 km) 2.	Medak Cathedral (28 km) 3.	Edupayala Temple (40 km) 4.	Narsapur Forest (35 km)', 'â€¢	Local restaurants in Medak â€¢	Highway restaurants on NH-65 â€¢	Traditional Telangana cuisine joints â€¢	Forest Department canteen', ''),
(114, 31, 5, 'Mrugavani National Park', 'Located just 20 km from Hyderabad, this urban national park spans 3.5 sq km. Perfect for day visits, featuring varied wildlife including spotted deer, wild boar, monitor lizards, and over 100 species of birds. Popular for its nature trails and educational programs.', 'Mrugavani National Park.jpg', 'Location: Chilkur, Hyderabad Coordinates: 17.3579Â° N, 78.3348Â° E', 'â€¢	No accommodation inside park â€¢	Numerous hotels in nearby Hyderabad â€¢	TSTDC Hotels â€¢	Resorts along Gandipet Lake', 'https://rangareddy.telangana.gov.in/tourist-place/mrugavani-national-park/', '1.	Osman Sagar Lake (5 km) 2.	Chilkur Balaji Temple (3 km) 3.	Golconda Fort (15 km) 4.	Taramati Baradari (12 km)', 'â€¢	Restaurants near Gandipet â€¢	Chilkur road eateries â€¢	Luxury hotels in Film Nagar â€¢	Local Telugu cuisine restaurants', ''),
(115, 31, 5, 'Kinnerasani Wildlife Sanctuary', 'Spread across 635.40 sq km of mixed deciduous forests around the Kinnerasani reservoir. Known for its diverse flora and fauna, including tigers, panthers, sloth bears, and various deer species. The sanctuary also features beautiful waterfalls and streams.', 'Kinnerasani Wildlife Sanctuary.png', 'Location: Kothagudem District Coordinates: 17.6747Â° N, 80.6579Â° E', 'â€¢	Kinnerasani Forest Rest House â€¢	TSTDC Haritha Resort â€¢	Paloncha town hotels â€¢	Eco-tourism cottages', 'https://tourism.telangana.gov.in/wild-life/KinnerasaniWildlifeSanctuary', '1.	Kinnerasani Dam (8 km) 2.	Paloncha town (15 km) 3.	Bhadrachalam Temple (60 km) 4.	Bogatha Waterfalls (80 km)', 'â€¢	Local restaurants in Paloncha â€¢	Traditional tribal cuisine outlets â€¢	Forest Department canteen â€¢	Highway restaurants', ''),
(116, 31, 5, 'Pakhal Wildlife Sanctuary', 'Established in 1952, Pakhal Wildlife Sanctuary covers 860 sq km of diverse terrain centered around the historic Pakhal Lake. The sanctuary is known for its population of panthers, sloth bears, nilgai, and various species of deer. The combination of lake ecosystem and forest habitat makes it a unique destination for wildlife enthusiasts and bird watchers.', 'Pakhal Wildlife Sanctuary.webp', 'Location: Warangal District Coordinates: 17.9234Â° N, 79.9876Â° E', 'â€¢	Pakhal Forest Rest House â€¢	TSTDC Haritha Resort at Pakhal Lake â€¢	Warangal city hotels (35 km) â€¢	Eco-tourism cottages near the lake', 'https://tourism.telangana.gov.in/wild-life/PakhalWildlifeSanctuary', '1.	Pakhal Lake (within sanctuary) 2.	Warangal Fort (40 km) 3.	Thousand Pillar Temple (38 km) 4.	Ramappa Temple (70 km)', 'â€¢	Lake View Restaurant â€¢	Local cuisine outlets near Pakhal â€¢	Warangal city restaurants â€¢	Forest Department canteen', ''),
(117, 2, 2, 'Meenakshi Amman Temple, Madurai', 'A historic 14-temple complex dedicated to Goddess Meenakshi and Lord Sundareswarar. Features stunning Dravidian architecture with 14 magnificent towers, the tallest being 170 feet high. The temple complex covers 45 acres and contains 33,000 sculptures. Famous for its intricate carved pillars, sacred tanks, and the celestial marriage celebration of Meenakshi and Sundareswarar.', 'Meenakshi Amman Temple, Madurai.jpg', 'Location: Madurai City Center Coordinates: 9.9195Â° N, 78.1193Â° E', 'â€¢	The Gateway Hotel Pasumalai â€¢	Heritage Madurai â€¢	Fortune Pandiyan Hotel â€¢	JC Residency â€¢	Budget hotels near temple', 'https://maduraimeenakshi.hrce.tn.gov.in//hrcehome/index_temple.php?tid=31962', '1.	Thirumalai Nayakkar Palace (2 km) 2.	Gandhi Museum (3 km) 3.	Vandiyur Mariamman Teppakulam (5 km) 4.	Alagar Kovil (21 km)', 'â€¢	Famous Jigarthanda shops â€¢	Murugan Idli Shop â€¢	Kumar Mess for authentic Tamil food â€¢	Temple street food vendors â€¢	The Modern Restaurant', ''),
(118, 2, 2, 'Brihadeeswarar Temple, Thanjavur', 'UNESCO World Heritage site built by Raja Raja Chola I. Known for its 216-foot high vimana topped with an 80-ton granite block. The temple showcases Chola architecture at its finest, with stunning frescoes, massive Nandi statue, and intricate stone carvings. The temple complex covers 36,000 sq ft.', 'Brihadeeswarar Temple, Thanjavur.jpg', 'Location: Thanjavur City Coordinates: 10.7827Â° N, 79.1317Â° E', 'â€¢	Svatma Heritage Hotel â€¢	Hotel Gnanam â€¢	Oriental Towers â€¢	Hotel Tamil Nadu â€¢	Ideal River View Resort', 'https://www.tamilnadutourism.tn.gov.in/destinations/brihadeeswara-temple', '1.	Thanjavur Palace (2 km) 2.	Saraswathi Mahal Library (2 km) 3.	Art Gallery and Museum (2.5 km) 4.	Gangaikonda Cholapuram (85 km)', 'â€¢	Bommi\\\'s Restaurant â€¢	Hotel Gnanam Restaurant â€¢	Thillana Restaurant â€¢	Local street food vendors â€¢	Traditional banana leaf meals', ''),
(119, 2, 2, 'Ramanathaswamy Temple, Rameswaram', 'One of the Char Dham pilgrimage sites, famous for its 22 holy water wells and the longest corridor among all Hindu temples (1,220 meters). Features Dravidian architecture with massive carved pillars and 12 towers. The temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva and is built where Rama worshipped Shiva.', 'Ramanathaswamy Temple, Rameswaram.jpg', 'Location: Rameswaram Island Coordinates: 9.2876Â° N, 79.3129Â° E', 'â€¢	Hotel Tamil Nadu â€¢	Daiwik Hotels â€¢	Hotel Brindavan Residency â€¢	Hotel Royal Park â€¢	TTDC Hotel', 'https://rameswaramramanathar.hrce.tn.gov.in/', '1.	Dhanushkodi Ghost Town (20 km) 2.	APJ Abdul Kalam Memorial (3 km) 3.	Pamban Bridge (2 km) 4.	Agnitheertham (0.5 km)', 'â€¢	Murugan Restaurant â€¢	Temple prasadam â€¢	Sea food restaurants â€¢	South Indian vegetarian hotels â€¢	Street food stalls', ''),
(120, 2, 2, 'Annamalaiyar Temple, Thiruvannamalai', 'One of the Pancha Bhoota Sthalams representing fire element. The temple complex covers 25 acres with four gateway towers, the tallest being 217 feet. Famous for Karthigai Deepam festival and its association with Saint Ramana Maharshi. The temple is built at the foot of Arunachala Hill.', 'Annamalaiyar Temple, Thiruvannamalai.jpeg', 'Location: Thiruvannamalai Coordinates: 12.2253Â° N, 79.0667Â° E', 'â€¢	Arunachala Hotel â€¢	Hotel Ramakrishna â€¢	Seshadri Ashram Guest House â€¢	Hotel Athithi â€¢	Sri Ramana Ashram', 'https://annamalaiyar.hrce.tn.gov.in/', '1.	Ramana Maharshi Ashram (2 km) 2.	Arunachala Hill (0.5 km) 3.	Girivalam Path (around the hill) 4.	Virupaksha Cave (3 km)', 'â€¢	Udupi restaurants â€¢	Hotel Saravana Bhavan â€¢	Local vegetarian restaurants â€¢	Ashram dining halls â€¢	Street food vendors', ''),
(121, 2, 2, 'Sri Ranganathaswamy Temple, Srirangam', 'The largest functioning Hindu temple in the world, covering 156 acres. Features 7 concentric walls, 21 gopurams with the main tower rising to 236 feet. Dedicated to Lord Ranganatha (Vishnu), the temple is the first of the 108 Divya Desams. Notable for its elaborate sculpture work and vast temple complex.', 'Sri Ranganathaswamy Temple, Srirangam.jpg', 'Location: Srirangam, Trichy Coordinates: 10.8624Â° N, 78.6916Â° E', 'â€¢	Grand Gardenia â€¢	Hotel Sangam â€¢	Breeze Residency â€¢	Hotel Sri Tower â€¢	Budget lodges near temple', 'https://srirangamranganathar.hrce.tn.gov.in/', '1.	Rock Fort Temple (6 km) 2.	Jambukeswarar Temple (4 km) 3.	Butterfly Park (5 km) 4.	Mukkombu Dam (18 km)', 'â€¢	Vasanta Bhavan â€¢	Punjabi Restaurant â€¢	Sri Krishna Vilas â€¢	Temple prasadam â€¢	Local vegetarian restaurants', ''),
(122, 2, 4, 'Chettinad Heritage ', 'Famous for its palatial mansions, unique architecture, and rich cultural heritage of the Nattukottai Chettiar community. The mansions feature Burma teak, Italian marble, and intricate carvings. The region is also renowned for its distinctive cuisine, handwoven cotton saris, and antique collections.', 'Chettinad Heritage.webp', 'Location: Sivaganga District Coordinates: 10.1755Â° N, 78.7347Â° E', 'â€¢	The Bangala Heritage Hotel â€¢	Visalam Heritage Hotel â€¢	Chidambara Vilas â€¢	Chettinad Mansion â€¢	Saratha Vilas', 'https://sarathavilas.com/discover-chettinad-heritage/', '1.	Athangudi Palace (5 km) 2.	Athangudi Tile Factory (5 km) 3.	Kanadukathan Palace (8 km) 4.	Pillayarpatti Temple (15 km)', 'â€¢	The Bangala Restaurant (authentic Chettinad cuisine) â€¢	Chidambara Vilas Restaurant â€¢	Local spice markets â€¢	Traditional banana leaf meals â€¢	Street food vendors', ''),
(123, 2, 4, 'Mahabalipuram (Mamallapuram)', 'UNESCO World Heritage site featuring 7th-8th century rock-cut temples and monuments. Home to the famous Shore Temple, Five Rathas, and Arjuna\\\'s Penance bas-relief. The site showcases the architectural excellence of Pallava dynasty with its monolithic rock sculptures.', '. Pocheram Wildlife Sanctuary.jpg', 'Location: Chengalpattu District Coordinates: 12.6269Â° N, 80.1927Â° E', 'â€¢	Radisson Blu Resort Temple Bay â€¢	Grande Bay Resort â€¢	Chariot Beach Resort â€¢	InterContinental Chennai â€¢	Local beach resorts', 'https://www.mahabalipuram.org/', '1.	Shore Temple Complex 2.	Krishna\\\'s Butter Ball 3.	Tiger Cave (5 km) 4.	Crocodile Bank (14 km)', 'â€¢	Moonrakers Restaurant â€¢	The Wharf â€¢	Sea Shore Garden Restaurant â€¢	Local seafood joints â€¢	Beach-side cafes', ''),
(124, 2, 4, 'Thanjavur Cultural Complex', 'Historic capital of the Chola Empire, known for its art, architecture, music, and dance traditions. Home to the famous Thanjavur painting style, bronze sculptures, and classical Bharatanatyam dance. The cultural complex includes the Royal Palace, Saraswati Mahal Library, and art galleries.', 'Thanjavur Cultural Complex.jpg', 'Location: Thanjavur City Coordinates: 10.7870Â° N, 79.1378Â° E', 'â€¢	Svatma Heritage â€¢	Ideal River View Resort â€¢	Hotel Gnanam â€¢	Hotel Tamil Nadu â€¢	Local heritage homestays', 'https://thanjavur.nic.in/heritage/', '1.	Brihadeeswara Temple (2 km) 2.	Royal Palace Museum (0.5 km) 3.	Saraswati Mahal Library (within complex) 4.	Art Gallery and Museum (1 km)', 'â€¢	Svatma\\\'s Traditional Restaurant â€¢	Thillana Veg Restaurant â€¢	Hotel Gnanam Restaurant â€¢	Local thali restaurants', ''),
(125, 2, 4, 'Madurai Heritage Zone', 'Ancient city centered around the Meenakshi Amman Temple, showcasing Tamil culture, literature, and art. Features historic mansions, traditional markets, and centuries-old streets patterns. The zone includes important heritage structures like the Thirumalai Nayakkar Palace and traditional trading centers.', 'Madurai Heritage Zone.jpg', 'Location: Madurai City Center Coordinates: 9.9252Â° N, 78.1198Â° E', 'â€¢	Heritage Madurai â€¢	The Gateway Hotel Pasumalai â€¢	Fortune Pandiyan Hotel â€¢	JC Residency â€¢	Sangam Hotel', 'https://www.maduraicorporation.co.in/tourism', '1.	Meenakshi Amman Temple (0.5 km) 2.	Thirumalai Nayakkar Palace (2 km) 3.	Gandhi Museum (3 km) 4.	Puthu Mandapam (1 km)', 'â€¢	Famous Jigarthanda shops â€¢	Murugan Idli Shop â€¢	Kumar Mess â€¢	Traditional banana leaf restaurants â€¢	Street food at Masi streets', ''),
(126, 2, 4, 'Poompuhar (Ancient Chola Port)', 'Ancient port city of the Chola dynasty, known for its maritime history and cultural significance. Features archaeological sites, art museum, and monuments depicting Tamil classical period. The site includes replicas of ancient Tamil architecture and sculptures.', 'Poompuhar (Ancient Chola Port).jpg', 'Location: Nagapattinam District Coordinates: 11.1397Â° N, 79.8500Â° E', 'â€¢	Hotel Tamil Nadu â€¢	Beach resorts â€¢	Government guest house â€¢	Local lodges â€¢	Homestays', 'http://tnarch.gov.in/', '1.	Silappathikaram Art Gallery 2.	Danish Fort (30 km) 3.	Tranquebar Beach (35 km) 4.	Nagore Dargah (15 km)', 'â€¢	Local seafood restaurants â€¢	Traditional Tamil restaurants â€¢	Beach-side eateries â€¢	Street food vendors', ''),
(127, 2, 4, 'Dakshin Chitra Heritage Museum', 'Living museum showcasing the art, architecture, crafts, and cultural heritage of South India. Features traditional houses from different states, craft demonstrations, and cultural performances. Regular workshops and events celebrate traditional arts and crafts.', 'Dakshin Chitra Heritage Museum.jpeg', 'Location: East Coast Road, Chennai Coordinates: 12.8245Â° N, 80.2323Â° E', 'â€¢	Taj Fisherman\\\'s Cove â€¢	Radisson Blu Resort â€¢	Local beach resorts â€¢	Chennai city hotels â€¢	ECR road resorts', 'https://www.dakshinachitra.net/', '1.	MGM Dizzee World (5 km) 2.	Muttukadu Boat House (8 km) 3.	Cholamandal Artists\\\' Village (10 km) 4.	Kovalam Beach (15 km)', 'â€¢	Wharf Restaurant â€¢	Bay View Restaurant â€¢	Local seafood joints â€¢	Traditional Tamil restaurants â€¢	Beach-side cafes', ''),
(128, 2, 1, 'Yelagiri Hills ', 'A hill station known for its adventure sports facilities, especially paragliding. Features 14 hairpin bends to reach the top, offering excellent terrain for mountain biking. The Yelagiri Adventure Sports Association organizes various activities throughout the year.Adventure Activities\\r\\nâ€¢	Paragliding\\r\\nâ€¢	Rock Climbing\\r\\nâ€¢	Trekking\\r\\nâ€¢	Mountain Biking\\r\\n', 'yelagiri-hills.jpg', 'Location: Vellore District Coordinates: 12.5845Â° N, 78.6476Â° E', 'â€¢	Sterling Yelagiri â€¢	Hotel Hill Top â€¢	Landmark Resort â€¢	TTDC Hotel Tamil Nadu â€¢	Echo Rock Resort', 'https://tirupathur.nic.in/tourist-place/yelagiri-hills/', '1.	Jalagamparai Falls (5 km) 2.	Velavan Temple (2 km) 3.	Nature Park (3 km) 4.	Punganoor Lake (1 km)', 'â€¢	Hill Top Restaurant â€¢	Sterling Resort Restaurant â€¢	Local Tamil cuisine joints â€¢	Lake View Restaurant â€¢	Street food stalls', ''),
(129, 2, 1, 'Kolli Hills', 'Famous for its 70 continuous hairpin bends, offering challenging terrain for off-road enthusiasts. Features numerous trekking trails, waterfalls, and dense forests. Known as \\\"Mountain of Death\\\" due to its challenging routes.Adventure Activities\\r\\nâ€¢	Off-road Driving\\r\\nâ€¢	Mountain Biking\\r\\nâ€¢	Trekking\\r\\nâ€¢	Cave Exploration\\r\\nâ€¢	Rappelling\\r\\n', 'Kolli Hills.jpg', 'Location: Namakkal District Coordinates: 11.2474Â° N, 78.3358Â° E', 'â€¢	Hotel Tamil Nadu â€¢	Black Thunder Resort â€¢	Nallathambi Resort â€¢	Forest Department Lodges â€¢	Local homestays', 'https://www.tamilnadutourism.tn.gov.in/destinations/kolli-hills', '1.	Agaya Gangai Falls (5 km) 2.	Arapaleeswarar Temple (2 km) 3.	Botanical Garden (3 km) 4.	Seekuparai View Point (4 km)', 'â€¢	Local hill restaurants â€¢	Tamil Nadu Hotel Restaurant â€¢	Traditional village eateries â€¢	Forest department canteen â€¢	Roadside dhabas', ''),
(130, 2, 1, 'Pichavaram Mangrove Forest ', 'Second largest mangrove forest in the world, covering 1,100 hectares. Perfect for water-based adventures through narrow canals and dense mangrove networks. Home to various bird species and aquatic life. Adventure Activities \\r\\nâ€¢	Kayaking\\r\\n â€¢	Boat Safari \\r\\nâ€¢	Bird Watching \\r\\nâ€¢	Nature Photography', 'Pichavaram.jpg', 'Location: Cuddalore District Coordinates: 11.4300Â° N, 79.7900Â° E', 'â€¢	TTDC Resort â€¢	Hotel Sathiyas â€¢	Beach resorts in Chidambaram â€¢	Local guesthouses â€¢	Eco lodges', 'https://cuddalore.nic.in/tourist-place/pichavaram/#:~:text=Pichavaram%20mangrove%20forest%20%7C%20Cuddalore%20District,View%20All', '1.	Chidambaram Temple (15 km) 2.	Silver Beach (20 km) 3.	Birdwatcher\\\'s Trail (on-site) 4.	Killai Backwaters (5 km)', 'â€¢	TTDC Restaurant â€¢	Local seafood joints â€¢	Traditional Tamil restaurants â€¢	Beach-side eateries â€¢	Street food stalls', ''),
(131, 2, 1, 'Meghamalai ', 'Known as the \\\"High Wavy Mountains,\\\" offering challenging trekking routes through tea and coffee plantations. Features pristine forests, wildlife, and stunning viewpoints. Perfect for wilderness camping and nature photography.Adventure Activities\\r\\nâ€¢	Wilderness Trekking\\r\\nâ€¢	Wildlife Spotting\\r\\nâ€¢	Nature Camping\\r\\nâ€¢	Photography Tours\\r\\nâ€¢	Night Trails\\r\\n', 'Meghamalai.jpeg', 'Location: Theni District Coordinates: 9.6513Â° N, 77.3624Â° E', 'â€¢	Meghamalai Resort â€¢	Forest Department Bungalow â€¢	Tea Estate Bungalows â€¢	Camping sites â€¢	Eco lodges', 'https://www.megamalai.com/#:~:text=Welcome%20to%20megamalai.com.&text=All%20the%20best%20and%20happy%20reading.&text=Meghamalai%20%26%20High%20Wavys%3A,meaning%20hills%20covered%20with%20clouds.', '1.	Cloud Mountain View Point (2 km) 2.	Vellimalai View Point (5 km) 3.	Manalar Dam (15 km) 4.	Tea Estates (on-site)', 'â€¢	Resort restaurants â€¢	Tea estate canteens â€¢	Local Tamil cuisine â€¢	Camp site cooking â€¢	Pack lunch options', ''),
(132, 2, 1, 'Mudumalai ', 'Part of the Nilgiri Biosphere Reserve, offering various wildlife adventures. Home to elephants, tigers, leopards, and various deer species. Features different vegetation types from moist deciduous to dry thorn forests.Adventure Activities\\r\\nâ€¢	Safari Tours\\r\\nâ€¢	Elephant Camp Visits\\r\\nâ€¢	Nature Walks\\r\\nâ€¢	Wildlife Photography\\r\\n', 'Mudumalai.jpg', 'Location: Nilgiris District Coordinates: 11.5977Â° N, 76.5344Â° E', 'â€¢	Jungle Hut â€¢	Wild Haven Resort â€¢	Bamboo Banks Farm â€¢	Forest Rest Houses â€¢	Safari Lodge', 'https://www.mudumalaitigerreserve.com/', '1.	Theppakadu Elephant Camp (5 km) 2.	Moyar River (8 km) 3.	Masinagudi (15 km) 4.	Ooty (32 km)', 'â€¢	Resort restaurants â€¢	Jungle camp food â€¢	Local cuisine restaurants â€¢	Forest department canteen â€¢	Traditional tribal food', ''),
(133, 2, 3, ' Marina Beach, Chennai', 'The second-longest urban beach in the world, stretching 13 km along the Bay of Bengal. Features historic Indo-Saracenic buildings, fishing villages, and the iconic lighthouse. Popular for sunrise walks, horse riding, and street food. The beach promenade comes alive in the evenings with numerous vendors and local entertainment.\\r\\n', 'Marina Beach, Chennai.jpg', 'Location: Chennai City Coordinates: 13.0500Â° N, 80.2824Â° E', 'â€¢	Leela Palace Chennai â€¢	The Park Chennai â€¢	Green Park Hotel â€¢	Hotel Palmgrove â€¢	Beach view guesthouses', 'https://chennai.nic.in/tourist-place/marina/', '1.	Santhome Basilica (2 km) 2.	Light House (on beach) 3.	Anna Square (1 km) 4.	Vivekananda House (2 km)', 'â€¢	Sundari Akka Kadai â€¢	Beach food stalls â€¢	Buhari Hotel â€¢	Saravana Bhavan', '');
